paragraphs.title: README
paragraphs.text:
%md

# JVMs Compare - Analyze Benchmarks using Apache Zeppelin

## Introduction
The Notebook is setup as a spark job (paragraph) followed by SQL query paragraphs. The spark paragraph extracts benchmark results and converts/squashes them into a single queryable view.

Comments in the spark paragraph help understand when is happening. There are comments that are prefixed with a *NOTE*. These comments indicate possible action being required.

Values marked as *NOTE* are:

1. *`project_path`*: This val represents the directory where the benchmark source was cloned from git. This directory is where each execution's pair of outputs: `benchmark-results` and `output` directories exist.
2. *`jdks`*: This val represents an array of JDK names. These JDKs were used for running the benchmarks. The order of the JDKs here matches the order (and prefixed number) for their results.  
  *For instance, GraalCE is the 3rd JDK run, per the project source (see: https://github.com/c-guntur/jvms-compare/blob/master/run-all.sh). Thus, GraalCE should be listed third in the *`jdks`* val below.*

## Information
The Notebook pulls numeric data from the CSV files by iterating over directories under the *`project_path/.../benchmark-results`*. In addition, some synthetic columns are added and transformations on loaded data are performed.

The loading begins with parsing a `template.csv` (from the Git project) located under the `project_path`. This empty CSV file creates the columns for the parser of subsequent CSV files to populate.

Columns:

* *Benchmark*: Name of the benchmark (this column is ***transformed*** to trim the name to the simple class name and method name of the benchmark).
* *Class*: Name of the Java class that contains a benchmark methods.
* *FullName*: Complete name of the benchmark method name.
* *Name*: Part of the method name describing the operation being benchmarked (*filter, sum, filterAndGroup etc.*)
* *Type*: The type of operation in the benchmarked method (*Serial or Parallel*)
* *Evaluation*: the evaluation of items in the benchmarked method (*Lazy, Stream or Eager*)
* *Collection*: The collection framework used (*EC = Eclipse Collections, JDK = Java Collections fromaework*)
* *Datatype*: The datatype of items in the benchmarked method (Object, Boxed or Primitive)
* *Mode*: Displays the benchmarking mode. Typically Throughput is the normal benchhmark. ***Higher throughput == better***.
* *Threads*: Displays the number of threads used to run the benchmarks.
* *Samples*: Displays the number of samples collected to fetch the benchmark statistics.
* *Score*: Displays the benchmark score.
* *Error*: Displays the benchmark error rate.
* *Units*: Displays the units used for measuring.
* *JDK*: Maps to the *`jdks`* to determine the JDK used, based on the CSV file prefix.
* *Size*: Directory name for each pair of outputs. (prefixed with ***1K_***, ***1M_*** etc.)

paragraphs.title: Verification Para: Counts of Benchmarks per Benchmark Class per JDK
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select count(*) from benchmarks
where 
  JDK="${JDK=OracleJDK,OracleJDK|GraalEE|GraalCE|AdoptOpenJDKHotspot|AdoptOpenJDKOpenJ9|OpenJDKHotspot|OpenJDKGraal|GraalEEC2}"
and 
  Benchmark like "%${BenchmarkClass=IntListFilter,IntListFilter|IntListSum|IntListTransform|PersonFilterOnly|PersonFilterAndGroup|PersonIntSummaryStats|PersonCombinedSummaryStats}%"
and 
  Size="${Size=1H_Named_JVM,1H_Named_JVM|1K_Anonymous_JVM|1M_Named_JVM|1M_Anonymous_JVM|1K_Anonymous_JVM_Heap_Controlled|1M_Anonymous_JVM_Heap_Controlled}"

paragraphs.title: Results Para: Max score per JDK for each Benchmark in each Size
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT Class, FullName, Score, Error, JDK 
FROM benchmarks
where 
  (Size, Benchmark, Score) IN
    (
      SELECT Size,Benchmark,MAX(Score) 
      FROM benchmarks
      WHERE 
        Size="${Size=1H_Named_JVM,1H_Named_JVM|1K_Anonymous_JVM|1M_Named_JVM|1M_Anonymous_JVM|1K_Anonymous_JVM_Heap_Controlled|1M_Anonymous_JVM_Heap_Controlled}"
      GROUP BY Size,Benchmark
    )
ORDER BY
  Class, FullName

paragraphs.title: Results Para: Max score per JDK per Type per Collection for each Benchmark in each Size
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT *
FROM benchmarks
where 
  (Size, Benchmark, Collection, Score) IN
    (
      SELECT Size, Benchmark, Collection, MAX(Score)
      FROM benchmarks
      WHERE 
        Size="${Size=1H_Named_JVM,1H_Named_JVM|1K_Anonymous_JVM|1M_Named_JVM|1M_Anonymous_JVM|1K_Anonymous_JVM_Heap_Controlled|1M_Anonymous_JVM_Heap_Controlled}"
      AND
        Type="${Type=Serial,Serial|Parallel}"
      AND 
        Collection="${Collection=EC,EC|JDK}"
      GROUP BY Size,Benchmark, Collection
    )
ORDER BY
  Class, FullName, Collection
